<headline>Special Weather Statement issued January 03 at 5:56AM CST  by NWS QuadCities</headline>
<description>...Bitterly Cold Start to the Day...
Temperatures in the negative single digits to near 10 below zero
early this morning, combined at times with a light south breeze,
will result in wind chill values in the teens below zero through
the morning commute for most areas. Some places may see wind
chills slip to near minus 25 degrees briefly.
Be sure to bundle up, covering exposed skin, as frostbite can
still happen within a half hour of exposure.</description>
